@here Faction goals for the rest of 2021

We’ve just lived trough the first half of 2021 (exact date was July 2nd) and this first half of the year has been very hectic for us with lots of changes happening as im sure you can agree. I feel like we've become slightly desultory where no one really has any idea where we as a family are going or  what we are aiming for. To give us some structure and framework, I’d like every faction in the family to think about what they need to improve upon on and set some goals to achieve by the end of the year. 

This can be thing like respect goals, chain goals, battle stats goals, improved communication etc

Please discuss this with your own council and let me know what your goals will be. 

I’ll give you an example: 
As for TW, we need to work on stats. We got more than enough respect and reaching higher up in the HOF faction rankings respect wise isn't important for us. We could hold energy spending competitions and perhaps setup a xanax “foundation” for people that meet certain requirements.

TW goals:
    • Focus on faction wide stat gains. Regular competitions are to be arranged as to  support hard core training. Minimum xanax/LSD requirements have been established and will BE followed  up on regularly. 
    • Have 6M respect by the end of the year. 135K will come from territories(165*822) meaning we need to make 265K from chains. I theory this means 4-5 10k’s. We will aim to hold December chain free as per tradition.

GW Goals:      
    • No respect goal
    • Complete a 25K chain
    • Become a top 100 faction

BW Goals: 
    • Have 2.2M respect by the end of the year. 80K will come from territories(132*613) meaning we need to make 135K from chains
    • Build a council
    • Achieve stability on the leadership front
    • Complete a 10K chain

Family goals:
    • Work on family cooperation and communication.  
    • Improve upon tribes and add several new parameters to track.  
    • Keep the family as 3 factions.
    • Create a system for promotions between the family factions
Commutation is something to do with punishment ain't it
Finally filled in the goals for BW and GW.
Oops, we didn’t keep the family as 3 factions! 😉
Did one better :p
Are we coming up with new goals? :P
Let's go trough our goals, still a couple of days in 2021 but i think we can recap

We did arrange training competitions but far from regular ones. We did haev one month of nothing but training since this goal was set but we could do more. The war with SA def had an effect on our training.
We've not been able to hold up the minimum xanax requirements atleast yet, but via recruiting and relocation of underperformers we're getting closer
Respect goal was met.
GW completed  both their goals as they did a 25K chain and are currently #92 in respect!
LW (then BW) are just 800 respect from their goal of 2.2M respect and will meet the set goal!
LW does have a wide council now albeit they need to me activated more
I think it's safe to say leadership is now stable after the merge with Lex
Correct me if im wrong but Lex did complete a 10k chain?
no we failed it at 6600 somewhere in there
but we will get the next one,  i'm extremely confident
I'd say we've improved somewhat on commutation between the factions. A concrete example are the monthly family newsletters keeping members informed on what's going on.
Tribes currently only track attacks but it's been fine tuned and now tracks them automatically. Adding more parameters is something for 2022
We didn't keep the family at 3 factions, instead we went one step further and increased it to 4 factions! 😄 (FEI, at the time we considered selling LW and using the money to upgrade GW)
There's still no clear guidelines on how to move up (or down) in the family and this is something we need to work on
maybe add a activity component to it along with BS
yeah for sure, this is a good idea!
Overall we did pretty well. These goal were setup in June so they were relatively easy to get right
Let's start making new goals after xmass!
and perhaps instead of yearly goals we set half year goals, as it's imposable to predict what the game will look like in a years time
I think ranked wars ranking might be a new goal to add?
I think @WR Leadership would agree, right now the goal we want is to raise the average battlestats of our current strength.
@390m average by ts with a majority on there,  I think doubling that this next year is attainable
700m stat average could be a goal?

And definitely wanna do ranked, we haven't talked 2022 goals alot yet,  but personally I think stats/rank should be our focus,  we have enough respect to bounce semi decent upgrade setups,  less chains,  moar trains
700m is insane
@Skulduggery_P We move this to GW council

Here’s my thoughts for BW
BW Half Year Goals
• Fund a DB from ranked warring profits (doesn't necessary need to go towards a DB)
• Reach Silver rank
• Have 1.4M respect by the half year.  125k will come from territories so 275k needs to be made from ranked wars
• Complete 20 ranked wars with a 75+% win rate
I have an ambitions plan for BW but we'll discuss that later 🙂
Sounds right up our alley then!
Let's start making goals for 2022 for each faction and the family as a whole.
The Wolverines
Gone Wild
Lex
Family

Goals for 2022, TW
    •  **7,200,000 Respect by the end of the year.**
        ◦ 1,000,000 Respect to be made out of which 497,130 will come of land (1362*365). 
        ◦ 502 870 respect to come from chains, with 8 chaining months that means 62900 per chaining month.
        ◦ This will allow us to unlock all upgrades in currently used branches and more. Possibility of a new branch added to the game this year, we are in a good place to unlock this. 
    •** Ranked Warring**
        ◦ Reach silver rank in ranked wars. 
        ◦ Make ranked wars the standard procedure for earning respect. Goal to do 2 ranked wars per month, or 16 ranked wars in 2022 
    • **Training**
        ◦ Several periods of 4 week non-stop training
            ▪️ March
            ▪️ June
            ▪️ September
            ▪️ December
        ◦ Arrange competitions to encourage hardcore training 
    • **Battle stats**
        ◦ Increase median stats by 1,000,000,000 
            ▪️ Achieved by members training and recruitment. 
    • **OC’s**
        ◦ 12 PA’s  (7 currently) 
        ◦ 6 PH’s (4 currently) 
    • **Council **
        ◦ Have a total of 3 members in council by the end of the year

Goals for 2022, The Wolverines Family 
    • Have each faction in the family be fully self sufficient
        ◦ Increase OC income by
            ▪ 30% for TW, currently about 1.2B per month ($1,56B)
            ▪ 50% for GW, currently about 350m per month ($525m)
            ▪ 100% for LW, currently about 150m per month ($300m)
    • Explore the possibility of turning BW into a revive faction
        ◦ Self-driven leaders need to be found who have a passion for reviving.
        ◦ May not compromise the strength on current faction leadership teams 
        ◦ To be fulfilled according to how King’s plans go.
    • Have 3 factions capable of fighting territorial wars on their own against equally strong or slightly stronger opponents.
    • Hold annual election of family spokesperson in July amongst leadership.
    • Solidify our position on the map by maintaining good relations to TGA, FSA and our neighbors.
    • Improve awareness of tribes.
    • Update faction graphics, descriptions, announcements pages and position names to be uniform across the family.
    • Have real time access to 90%+ of family members battles stats and NNB via either TS or TornPro
That all looks really good.  I like the idea of warring every two weeks and seeing how high we can take this.

Has each faction finalized their year/half-year goals?
We should update WHO's now that we've cemented their role as a revive faction.
I also wanted to add a family goal:
Wanted to add on a family goal:
Over 66.6% of liquid family assets dedicated to investments yielding 80%+ annual ROI
We have a few trusted leadership members such as Badazzb who are yet to max bank investment so could always allocate funds for her to fill up & donate x amount of the interest back into the family

I would totally be willing to take my personal funds out of the bank and put them in my company, vault, or in stocks that im working towards to be able to do that. to hold all of it and give all of the interest back into family
i dont even set my investments like i should. I only do them weekly so if i need the money i can access it. so its no sweat off my back to be able to do that for the family

@everyone 2024 goal threads. 
In your threads, please reflect on your 2023 goals. Mark which ones were successfully completed. Evaluate and discuss those that were unsuccessful.
Then, discuss new goals for 2024. 
My uni has been forcing this format for goals onto me so I'm gonna force it onto yall, please follow the SMART format for goals. That is, goals should be:
S - Specific  
M - Measurable (goal should be objectively measurable, ie. "win 25 ranked wars" instead of "kick ass in RWs"
A - Attainable (goal should be reasonably accomplishable, ie. "progress to diamond rank" instead of "be the #1 RW faction in all of Torn") 
R - Relevant (to progressing the faction/family)
T - Time bound (within the next year)

As a reminder, please discuss in threads. **Do not** chat in this channel.
